metadata.name: Dually #39
metadata.description:
Each mint is audioreactive visuals paired with a beat that has a dual nature: you might start with a slightly more “sinister” vibe or a slightly “bouncy” vibe, which sets the tone with the beat's bassline and the colors of the visualization

From there, the “instruments” are features that pull from a set of possible variants. The beat that you end up with when you mint is layered together from those features

All of these audio tracks are composed by hand the old-fashioned human-made way using sampling, synths, soul, and Ableton Live

The visualization is one of seven variants and is are driven by the instruments in the beat

Click to pause and mute, or to see what rad visual moments you can capture

P5.js + chroma.js + Tone.js + beats

metadata.name: One Tezo Drawings_65+ #48
metadata.description:
The One Tezo Drawings project is a variation of the “Desenhos de um Real” project (2006- ). In it, the artist sets the price of his work by making a rational calculation, equating his artistic production with a consumer good detached from the art world .
In this case, the calculation is based on the amount charged per hour of work from the minimum wage in the United States. Thus, a drawing that took X hours to produce (Wt) will have its price fixed at USD 15.00 * Wt divided by the value in Dollars of one Tezo (Dt) at the time of publication. But for the final price to be 1.00 Tez, the total production time value (Wt) will be divided by the number of editions (Ed). Therefore, the number of editions is defined by the following formula: 1.00 Tez = (Wt*15/Dt)/Ed ==> 

Ed=Wt*15/Dt 


For this particular project:
Permutation of 10 to 16 mirrored layers.

Wt= 6.5
Dt= 2.00
Ed= 6.5*15/2 = 49

Press J or P to save a 1500x1500px image

NFT Licence 2.0 - Diego de los Campos

metadata.name: La Veranada #27
metadata.description:
My mother lives in the countryside with her husband and her work is the breeding and grazing of goats, cows and horses. They live a cyclical life marked by two big stages during their livestock year: "La Veranada" and "La Invernada".
The "invernada" is the place where they live during what we could call the long winter, that is, from April to November. "La Invernada" is below, in the plains, in the pampas, in accessible places, where it is easy to supply the animals with fodder.
"La Veranada" is the place where they go during the long summer, from November to April, it is above, in the mountain ranges, on the heights, where the summer pastures abound, where they go for months to take care, alone, of the goats, cows and calves.
The transfer of the animals to the summer pasture is called "Arreo", my mother's husband guides the animals on his horse. The "Arreo" lasts about 5 days.
In both places they live in what they call "el puesto". "El puesto" is their home.
In "La veranada", "El puesto" is simple. A common living room, with a wood stove, a table, some chairs and shelves to store flour, *"mate" and salt. A small bedroom replenishes the strength worn out by the daily work. Water for drinking, cooking and washing is drawn from a nearby stream.
Work is abundant. As a common element, both in winter and summer, my mother's husband rides a horse daily and, accompanied by his dogs, goes to "watch" the cattle.
As a final point I wanted to thank you for taking your time and reading the story behind this project that I really enjoyed doing it, and on my tw profile you can read this story with real photos.

*Mate: is an Argentinean infusion, which is present all day long in the life of people who live in the countryside. It give you energy.

metadata.description:

This project is inspired by the delicate balance between daily habits and life-turning points.

"Rhythms" invites you to reflect on the beautiful complexity that fills our vital experience, on the millions of tiny details that bring texture to our journey causing balance or disruption.

metadata.name: Reflejos #34
metadata.description:
Reflejos es un proyecto de arte generativo diseñado para existir en la blockchain de Tezos. Este proyecto se aloja en la plataforma fx(hash) y genera obras de arte únicas utilizando un algoritmo y un sistema numérico hexadecimal que se crea con cada nuevo token.

Este proyecto fue desarrollado utilizando la librería p5.js de JavaScript, creada por Lauren Lee McCarthy. Reflejos es el resultado de la interacción entre la percepción humana y un conjunto de reglas interpretadas por la máquina.

Inspirado por la experiencia de caminar junto al mar y los estados de calma y contemplación que esta actividad puede evocar, Reflejos busca entrelazar a los espectadores con las obras de la colección. 

La intención es motivar al espectador a explorar su interior y descubrir momentos de apertura perceptiva. 

El objetivo es que la obra provoque una sensación de calma y claridad en el espectador a través de una conexión íntima y personal.

metadata.name: Sleepless #76
metadata.description:
Sleepless is a generative art project made from p5.js. Inspired by the artist's travels, the project emulates a window view of a distant city at night. Variations include randomization of different window elements (frames and bars) and city elements (buildings, planes and ships). It is also mintable in several foreground and background colors. The colors and dithering were selected to create a charcoal texture.

Press 'S' to download a high res PNG.
Due to the preview image being compressed to fit your window size, the dithering may look different from the high res PNG.
